description: The uptime utility displays the current time, the length of time the system has been up, the number of users, and the load average of the system over the last 1, 5, and 15 minutes.

sections.title: NAME
codeBlocks:
uptime â€“ show how long system has been running
     uptime
     The uptime utility displays the current time, the length of time the
     system has been up, the number of users, and the load average of the
     system over the last 1, 5, and 15 minutes.
	   $ uptime
	   11:23AM  up	3:01, 8 users, load averages: 21.09, 15.43, 12.79
     w(1)
     The uptime command appeared in 3.0BSD.
